# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

The Mistral Instruct v0.3 / Nemo format (`[INST]`/`[/INST]` user turns, `[TOOL_CALLS][{json array}]` tool calls, `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` for tool definitions) currently falls through to the autoparser in `common/chat.cpp`. A dedicated specialized handler will provide more robust, explicit parsing with PEG grammar support, matching the pattern used by Ministral 3 and other specialized handlers.

The key distinguisher from Ministral 3 (which uses `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]name[ARGS]{json}`) is the **absence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`** and the use of JSON-array-wrapped tool calls.

## Files to Modify

1. **`common/chat.cpp`** — Add handler function + detection clause
2. **`tests/test-chat.cpp`** — Expand test cases for the Nemo template

No new files needed. The existing Jinja template at `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` serves as the reference. No changes to `src/llama-chat.h` or any existing handler functions.

## Step 1: Add Handler Function in `common/chat.cpp`

Insert a new static function **after line 940** (after `common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`, before `common_chat_params_init_gpt_oss`):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
    const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs)
{
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = { "[TOOL_CALLS]" };

    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = true;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        auto generation_prompt = p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt);

        // JSON schema response format
        if (inputs.json_schema.is_object() && !inputs.json_schema.empty()) {
            return generation_prompt
                + p.content(p.schema(p.json(), "response-format", inputs.json_schema))
                + p.end();
        }

        // Tool call mode: [TOOL_CALLS][{"name": "...", "arguments": {...}, "id": "..."}]
        if (has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE) {
            auto tool_calls = p.standard_json_tools(
                /* section_start      = */ "[TOOL_CALLS]",
                /* section_end        = */ "",
                /* tools              = */ inputs.tools,
                /* parallel_tool_calls= */ inputs.parallel_tool_calls,
                /* force_tool_calls   = */ inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED,
                /* name_key           = */ "name",
                /* args_key           = */ "arguments",
                /* array_wrapped      = */ true,
                /* function_is_key    = */ false,
                /* call_id_key        = */ "id",
                /* gen_call_id_key    = */ "",
                /* parameters_order   = */ {"name", "arguments", "id"}
            );

            auto force = inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED;
            return generation_prompt
                + (force ? p.eps() : p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]")))
                + tool_calls + p.end();
        }

        // Content-only mode
        include_grammar = false;
        return generation_prompt + p.content(p.rest()) + p.end();
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;

        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            foreach_function(inputs.tools, [&](const json & tool) {
                const auto & function = tool.at("function");
                auto         schema   = function.at("parameters");
                builder.resolve_refs(schema);
            });
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });

        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    return data;
}
```

### Design rationale
- **`standard_json_tools`**: Reuses the existing PEG builder helper that already handles JSON-array-wrapped tool calls with flat keys (`name`, `arguments`, `id`). This avoids ~70 lines of manual PEG construction.
- **`parameters_order = {"name", "arguments", "id"}`**: Matches the exact field order the Jinja template emits.
- **`array_wrapped = true`**: The tool calls are wrapped in `[...]`.
- **`section_end = ""`**: The `]` closing the array is handled by `array_wrapped`; `</s>` is the eos_token handled by the tokenizer.
- **No reasoning/thinking support**: The V3/Nemo format has no `[THINK]`/`[/THINK]` markers.

## Step 2: Add Detection Clause in `common/chat.cpp`

Insert a new detection block in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` at **line 1645** (after the Ministral 3 check, before the GPT-OSS check). Note: line numbers will shift by ~70 lines from Step 1.

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v3 / Nemo - uses [INST]/[/INST] and [TOOL_CALLS][{json}] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

### Detection logic
| Marker | Check | Why |
|--------|-------|-----|
| `[INST]` | present | Confirms Mistral instruct format |
| `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` | present | Confirms V3-style tool calling (not Llama2) |
| `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` | absent | Distinguishes from Ministral 3 and V7 |

## Step 3: Update Tests in `tests/test-chat.cpp`

The existing test block at lines 3139-3148 already tests the Nemo template via autoparser. Since the new specialized handler will now intercept this template, these tests will exercise the new handler. The existing tests should continue to pass as-is. No test changes are strictly required, but we can add additional coverage.

Add new test cases **after the existing Nemo tests** (after line 3148, before the Functionary v3.2 block):

```cpp
// Additional Mistral Instruct v3 tests (specialized handler)
{
    auto tst = peg_tester("models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja", detailed_debug);

    // Parallel tool calls with IDs
    tst.test("[TOOL_CALLS][{\"name\": \"special_function\", \"arguments\": {\"arg1\": 1}, \"id\": \"aaa111bbb\"}, "
             "{\"name\": \"special_function_with_opt\", \"arguments\": {\"arg1\": 1, \"arg2\": 2}, \"id\": \"ccc222ddd\"}]")
        .parallel_tool_calls(true)
        .tools({ special_function_tool, special_function_tool_with_optional_param })
        .expect_tool_calls({
            { "special_function", "{\"arg1\":1}", "aaa111bbb" },
            { "special_function_with_opt", "{\"arg1\":1,\"arg2\":2}", "ccc222ddd" },
        })
        .run();
}
```

## Verification

1. **Build**: `cmake -B build && cmake --build build --parallel`
2. **Run chat template tests**: `./build/bin/test-chat-template` (validates basic template formatting)
3. **Run chat tests**: `./build/bin/test-chat` (validates PEG parsing, tool calls, reconstruction for the Nemo template)
4. **Verify detection**: Run with debug logging enabled and confirm the log message `"Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3"` appears when processing the Nemo template

